To the most beautiful woman in the world, 
This does feel really yet and it probably never will. My best friend. My biggest supporter, no matter the circumstances. I have so many beautifully vivid memories of you in the 30 years since you had me. Never wanting for anything but my Mommy. Always looking up to you even if you we’re shorter than me. I hope you are watching Braveheart right now all cozy in a warm, comfy bed with your Mommy, Daddy, Leo and Tinker. I’m everything I am, because you loved me. You live in me forever. I love you to the moon and back. We will see each other one day and I can’t wait to feel your bony back on my hands again. Rest easy my Momma 🪽💜
